# About Me

I am a Cybersecurity enthusiast with a strong focus on **Blue Team Operations**, dedicated to understanding how modern threats operate and how organizations can effectively **detect, investigate, and respond** to security incidents.

My interests span across **Security Operations Center (SOC) workflows**, **Detection Engineering**, **Threat Hunting**, **Incident Response**, **Digital Forensics (DFIR)**, **Windows and Linux Security**, **Active Directory**, **SIEM platforms**, **Security Automation**, and **Cloud Security**.

I am passionate about building practical cybersecurity knowledge through continuous learning, hands-on labs, technical documentation, and real-world methodologies. I enjoy transforming complex security concepts into structured, easy-to-understand resources that can support students, analysts, and cybersecurity professionals.

My goal is to continuously improve my technical skills while contributing high-quality educational content to the cybersecurity community.

